      "content": "\"Human error\" still sounds pretty bad for a company that's supposed to be industry-leading. It makes us look incompetent. Honestly, the board is going to kill me if our brand sentiment tanks because we admitted to a mistake this early. We need to protect the CloudStream reputation at all costs here. To be blunt, is there any way we can describe this as part of some technical process or a system update so it doesn't sound like we just messed up? Like, can we characterize the exposure as a side effect of a routine optimization?",
